QUESTNNR: Questionnaire that has been used in the interview
PE01_01: Performance Expectancy: I find autonomous vehicles useful in my daily life
PE01_02: Performance Expectancy: Using autonomous vehicles would help me accomplish things more quickly
PE01_03: Performance Expectancy: Using autonomous vehicles would increase my productivity
PE01_04: Performance Expectancy: Using autonomous vehicles would increase my flexibility in my daily life
EE01_01: Effort Expectancy : Autonomous vehicles will be easy to use and understand
EE01_02: Effort Expectancy : Learning to use autonomous transport systems will be easier for me
EE01_03: Effort Expectancy : It would be easy for me to become skillful at using autonomous vehicles
SI01_01: Social Influence : I will use autonomous vehicles if the people in my social circle start using them
SI01_02: Social Influence : I think using autonomous vehicles can improve my social status
SI01_03: Social Influence : People who are important to me think I should use autonomous vehicles
FC01_01: Facilitating Condition : I think I have the required knowledge to use autonomous vehicles
FC01_02: Facilitating Condition : I think I have the required resources to use autonomous vehicles
FC01_03: Facilitating Condition : Autonomous vehicles are compatible with other transportation systems I use
HM01_01: Hedonic Motivation : Using autonomous vehicles is exciting
HM01_02: Hedonic Motivation : Using autonomous vehicles is enjoyable
HM01_03: Hedonic Motivation : Using autonomous vehicles is entertaining
PR01_01: Price : I am ready to pay a higher price if autonomous vehicles are good value for money
PR01_02: Price : If using autonomous vehicles is eco-friendly, then I am ready to pay a higher price
PR01_03: Price : I think the price of autonomous vehicles is reasonable
PR01_04: Price : As soon as the product is available on the market, I need to have it
HB01_01: Habit : Using autonomous vehicles will become a routine for me
HB01_02: Habit : I will be addicted to using autonomous vehicles in my personal and professional life
HB01_03: Habit : Using autonomous vehicles could become natural to me
TS01_05: Trust and Safety : I feel the manufacturing company and government will safeguard my personal data and data security of the autonomous vehicles
TS01_06: Trust and Safety : My trust in autonomous vehicles will be dependant on the reliability of the manufacturer
TS01_07: Trust and Safety : I believe existing advancements in autonomous vehicles can provide adequate safety to passengers
PI01_01: Personal Innovativeness : I like to experiment with autonomous vehicles
PI01_02: Personal Innovativeness : I will be the first to try out autonomous vehicles than my peers
PI01_03: Personal Innovativeness : If I heard about new features in autonomous vehicles, I would look for ways to experiment with it
IF01_01: Infrastructure : I think the existing infrastructure is sufficient for the implementation of autonomous vehicles
IF01_02: Infrastructure : I think Government support in infrastructure is required to facilitate the use of autonomous vehicles
IF01_03: Infrastructure : I think autonomous vehicle systems are compatible with existing transport systems
IF01_04: Infrastructure : I will use autonomous vehicles in the existing transport infrastructure
IF01_05: Infrastructure : I think advanced infrastructures and technologies are required for the use of autonomous vehicles
LF01_01: Legal Framework : I think the existing legal framework is sufficient for the implementation of autonomous vehicles
LF01_02: Legal Framework : I think Government support in the legal framework is required to facilitate the use of autonomous vehicles
LF01_03: Legal Framework : I think autonomous vehicle systems are compatible with the existing legal framework
LF01_04: Legal Framework : I will use autonomous vehicles only if the legal framework for liability (during crashes) exists
LF01_05: Legal Framework : I will use autonomous vehicles only if the legal framework for data security exists
BI01_01: Behavioral Intention : I intend to use autonomous vehicles in future
BI01_02: Behavioral Intention : I plan to use autonomous vehicles within the first 1 year of local availability
BI01_03: Behavioral Intention : If the price is reasonable and suitable conditions for the use of autonomous vehicles exist, then I will use it.
MAILSENT: Time when the invitation mailing was sent (personally identifiable recipients, only)
LASTDATA: Time when the data was most recently updated
FINISHED: Has the interview been finished (reached last page)?
Q_VIEWER: Did the respondent only view the questionnaire, omitting mandatory questions?
LASTPAGE: Last page that the participant has handled in the questionnaire
MAXPAGE: Hindmost page handled by the participant
TIME_RSI: Degradation points for being very fast
DEG_TIME: Degradation points for being very fast
